methods.name: updateApplication
methods.desc: addressUdpater from global biatec configuration is allowed to update application

methods.name: setAddressUdpater
methods.desc: Top secret account with which it is possible update contracts or identity provider

methods.name: setPaused
methods.desc: Kill switch. In the extreme case all services (deposit, trading, withdrawal, identity modifications and more) can be suspended.

methods.name: setAddressGov
methods.desc: Execution address with which it is possible to opt in for governance

methods.name: setAddressExecutive
methods.desc: Execution address with which it is possible to change global biatec fees

methods.name: setAddressExecutiveFee
methods.desc: Execution fee address is address which can take fees from pools.

methods.name: setBiatecFee
methods.desc:
Fees in 9 decimals. 1_000_000_000 = 100%
Fees in 9 decimals. 10_000_000 = 1%
Fees in 9 decimals. 100_000 = 0,01%


Fees are respectful from the all fees taken to the LP providers. If LPs charge 1% fee, and biatec charges 10% fee, LP will receive 0.09% fee and biatec 0.01% fee

methods.name: sendOnlineKeyRegistration
methods.desc:
addressExecutiveFee can perfom key registration for this LP pool


Only addressExecutiveFee is allowed to execute this method.

methods.name: withdrawExcessAssets
methods.desc:
If someone deposits excess assets to this smart contract biatec can use them.


Only addressExecutiveFee is allowed to execute this method.

args.name: asset
args.desc: Asset to withdraw. If native token, then zero

args.name: amount
args.desc: Amount of the asset to be withdrawn
